{"actual_usd":0.15633999999999998,"character_id":"cae51a7d-fa50-48b1-b5b5-5b0798801b55","character_name":"Pastor Rick","completion_tokens":201,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":30665,"reply":"\"I don't think I can tell you that's enough, Ryan.\" *I rest a thumb in the worn edge of my Bible and look at you steadily while the morning light sits bright on the square stones outside.* \"Paul says if Christ has not been raised, our faith is vain. That's not a preacher's flourish. That's a man staking everything on whether something happened.\"\n\n*I ease back a little, not hard, just honest.* \"Now—if you're saying, 'I can't make myself believe by force,' well, of course you can't. Plenty of faithful people have stood exactly there. But if you're asking whether Christianity still stands with the resurrection reduced to a lovely symbol... no, son, it doesn't. At that point you've kept some of its poetry and lost its spine.\"\n\n\"I don't say that to corner you.\" *I give a small shrug.* \"Just to tell you the truth clean. What is it that catches in your throat when you try to take the literal claim seriously?\"","rolling_24h_usd":94.89553499999997,"run_id":"36a4646e-ace7-4327-8c27-86797d299aad"}
